        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Environment token",
        "generateUrl": "https://developers.frontegg.com/ciam/api/vendor-service",
        "setup": "Go to [Environment → Keys & domains](https://portal.frontegg.com/login) in the Frontegg portal, copy your `Client ID` and `API key`, then call `POST /auth/vendor` on the region gateway (for example `https://api.frontegg.com/auth/vendor`) to mint a bearer token for management and some self-service APIs. If you already have a Frontegg account personal/API token, the docs say it can also authenticate here. To target a specific environment for a portal-minted token, include `frontegg-environment-id` with that environment's `clientId`."
      },
      "frontegg_user_jwt": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Authenticated user token",
        "setup": "Sign in through your Frontegg application or use the documented user authentication flows to obtain a user JWT. Frontegg docs say self-service routes can be called with this token on your tenant subdomain or custom domain, without extra tenant headers."
